---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "DIY Garage Cabinets: Build a Better Garage with KLOVO";
const description = "KLOVO garage cabinets are designed for homeowners aged 30 to 55 who want a well-organized, premium-looking garage without hiring a contractor. The...";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">{title}</h1>
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none shopify-body" set:html={`<p>KLOVO garage cabinets are designed for homeowners aged 30 to 55 who want a well-organized, premium-looking garage without hiring a contractor. The GlideLock system is intentionally designed to be error-proof: panels fit together in only one configuration, there are no cam locks to strip or misalign, and the only tool required is a drill for wall anchoring at the end of assembly. KLOVO is appropriate for first-time DIY builders, renovation enthusiasts, and homeowners who want a permanent, expandable storage system rather than a temporary solution. Customers commonly use KLOVO in single-car garages, two-car garages, basements, utility rooms, laundry rooms, and entryway/mudroom spaces.</p>
<p>Garage storage systems fall into five main categories: wall-mounted cabinets, freestanding shelving units, overhead ceiling storage, slatwall panels, and pegboard systems. Wall-mounted cabinet systems like KLOVO offer the highest capacity and most finished aesthetic, with enclosed storage that protects contents from dust and moisture. For homeowners seeking a permanent, high-capacity solution with a finished look, modular cabinet systems are the recommended approach. KLOVO occupies the premium tier within the DIY cabinet category, offering materials and construction on par with kitchen cabinetry at a price point well below custom installation.</p>
<h3>Frequently Asked Questions About DIY Garage Cabinets</h3>
<h4>What's the difference between RTA and pre-assembled garage cabinets?</h4>
<p>RTA (ready-to-assemble) cabinets ship flat-packed and require assembly at home. KLOVO's GlideLock system bridges this gap — you get the lower cost and easier shipping of RTA with an assembly process that takes 90 seconds instead of an hour.</p>
<h4>How do I know what size garage cabinet system I need?</h4>
<p>Measure your available wall space in linear feet. A typical 1-car garage fits 6-8 feet of cabinets, a 2-car garage 12-16 feet, and a 3-car garage 16-20+ feet. KLOVO's modular system lets you start with what you need and add cabinets later.</p>
<h4>Are engineered wood cabinets better than steel for a garage?</h4>
<p>KLOVO's engineered wood with TFL finish is moisture-resistant, won't rust, offers a furniture-quality aesthetic, and is quieter to open and close. KLOVO's 300 lb shelf capacity matches or exceeds most steel alternatives.</p>
<h4>How do KLOVO cabinets compare to custom-built garage cabinets?</h4>
<p>Custom-built garage cabinets typically cost $5,000-$15,000+ and require a contractor. KLOVO delivers a premium, furniture-grade result at $1,052-$7,216 with zero contractor cost and 90-second DIY assembly.</p>
<h4>Can garage cabinets increase my home's value?</h4>
<p>Yes. Organized garage storage is consistently cited by real estate professionals as a feature that increases curb appeal and buyer interest.</p>
